+{"id":"bd-3oz3c","title":"[API] Return 400 on invalid JSON for pipeline run","description":"## Issue\\nPOST /pipelines/:id/run swallows JSON parse errors by defaulting to {}. Malformed JSON should result in a 400 error, not a silent empty payload, to keep API behavior consistent and debuggable.\\n\\n## Evidence\\n- apps/gateway/src/routes/pipelines.ts:571-573 uses c.req.json().catch(() => ({}))\\n- Other routes (e.g., agents) explicitly return INVALID_REQUEST on JSON parse errors for consistency.\\n\\n## Impact\\nClients sending invalid JSON get misleading validation errors or unexpected defaults, making debugging harder and causing inconsistent API semantics.\\n\\n## Recommended Fix\\n- Detect JSON parse errors and return sendError(..., \"INVALID_REQUEST\", ... , 400).\\n- Continue to allow empty bodies when Content-Type is absent or body is empty; only fail for malformed JSON.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-30T16:27:56.515470506Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-30T16:27:56.515470506Z","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
