+{"id":"bd-7bb95","title":"[Security] Derive user identity from auth context in pipelines/notifications","description":"## Issue\\nUser identity is accepted via query parameters (user_id/recipient_id) without verifying against auth context. This allows impersonation once auth is enabled, and leaks user-scoped data when auth is disabled.\\n\\n## Evidence\\n- apps/gateway/src/routes/pipelines.ts:569-583 (POST /pipelines/:id/run uses user_id query)\\n- apps/gateway/src/routes/pipelines.ts:776-812 (approve endpoint uses user_id query)\\n- apps/gateway/src/routes/notifications.ts:302-415 (preferences/read endpoints use user_id/recipient_id query)\\n\\n## Impact\\nAny caller can act on behalf of another user by supplying a different user_id or recipient_id.\\n\\n## Recommended Fix\\n- Read userId from auth context (c.get(\"auth\").userId) and ignore/validate query params.\\n- Return 403 if a provided user_id/recipient_id does not match authenticated user (unless admin).\\n- Consider removing user_id/recipient_id query params from public API in favor of auth-derived identity.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-30T16:27:42.926471007Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-30T16:27:42.926471007Z","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
