+{"id":"bd-qvgym","title":"[Security] Gate /setup/install to admin or localhost","description":"## Issue\\n/setup/install and /setup/install/batch trigger tool installation that runs \"bash -c\" with installer commands. When JWT_SECRET/GATEWAY_ADMIN_KEY are not set, auth middleware allows all requests, so these endpoints are effectively public.\\n\\n## Evidence\\n- apps/gateway/src/routes/setup.ts:163-218 (install endpoints, no auth check)\\n- apps/gateway/src/services/setup.service.ts:721-736 (executes install command via Bun.spawn [\"bash\", \"-c\"])\\n\\n## Impact\\nRemote callers can trigger tool installation if the service is exposed without auth config, leading to arbitrary command execution via installer scripts.\\n\\n## Recommended Fix\\n- Require auth context + admin for install endpoints (e.g., check c.get(\"auth\").isAdmin).\\n- If auth is disabled, explicitly deny install endpoints unless a dev-only allowlist is set (e.g., allow loopback or ENABLE_SETUP_INSTALL_UNAUTH=true).\\n- Ensure error is 401/403 with clear message.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-30T16:27:27.868763311Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-30T16:31:35.044885456Z","closed_at":"2026-01-30T16:31:35.044796611Z","close_reason":"Require admin or ENABLE_SETUP_INSTALL_UNAUTH for setup installs; add tests","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
